// COMPILING THE VIS (WUAXIS §4): `compileSpec` walks the node tree from the root, compiles each
// node (dataflow/graph.compileNode — its arrange op, its plots) and appends the render SINK — one
// logical dataflow graph of operator DESCRIPTIONS, nothing executed, no cell assigned. That graph
// is what the optimizer will lower (substrate · fold · SCC, WUSCHED_IMPL); today `compileOps`
// lowers it directly and the C5 scheduler runs it. `renderSpec` is the thin driver:
// compile → lower → schedule → read the sink cell.
